  "texts": [
    "For J2/J1 < 1/2, the system follows the standard 6-state clock model: low-T FM (Z + 6 FM), intermediate QLRO, and high-T PM phases.",
    "For J2/J1 > 1/2, five distinct phases emerge, including Z + 6 AFM ⊕ Z2 NM at low T and critical QLRO ⊕ Z2 NM at intermediate T. Furthermore, a narrow non-critical Z2 NM phase appears at smaller J2/J1 > 1/2 (see (b)).",
    "Most notably, a third non-critical phase (Z - 6 AFM ⊕ Z2 NM) emerges (the lobe in (a)), where effective Z6 angles shift from 2kπ/6 to (2k+1)π/6.",
    "Solid, dashed, and dotted lines indicate BKT, Ising, and first-order transitions, respectively.",
    "The solid black lines with red '+' symbols indicate the Landau-incompatible continuous transition, see text, with the black squares indicating its extent."
  ],
